# Cursor Rules for StillNatty Astro Project

## Documentation Files
- NEVER proactively create documentation files (*.md) or README files
- Only create documentation files if explicitly requested by the user
- This prevents cluttering the repository with unnecessary documentation

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new code files
- Follow the existing patterns in the codebase
- Use Bun as the package manager (not npm or yarn)

## Astro Best Practices
- Use Astro components (.astro files) for UI components
- Keep TypeScript logic in separate .ts files when appropriate
- Follow the existing directory structure in src/

## Cloudflare Integration
- Be mindful that this deploys to Cloudflare Pages
- Use appropriate Cloudflare features when relevant
- Test locally with `bun preview` before deploying

